["Data Platform Engineer | Consultor - About the vacancy
Job Description

The Data & Analytics department has been going through a huge restructuring in recent times. We created teams, remodeled some that already existed, created roles and even managed to bring in a director!

Everyone knows that over time, the need for more insight has and will continue to result in many petabytes of analytics data that need to be cleaned, stored and served with minimal latency. Thinking about abstracting the processes involved in these stages, comes the concept of the Data Platform in D&A. A Big Data solution that guarantees data reliability, scalability and ease of use (low and even no code in the future).

We are currently organizing ourselves to give form to this Platform which, in a way, has been built in a fragmented way and at a much slower pace than what we really need to employ in the board to move forward in our mission. You'll work on all aspects of systems, from services to back-end data stores, analytics and logging.

If you are a person with a disability and are unsure if you can apply, know that all jobs at Take Blip are inclusive! We look forward to your registration!

Responsibilities and assignments

We will rely on all your experience to help us in the development and evolution of our Data Platform. We want to reach a level where it can provide greater autonomy and speed, reducing complexity for analytics engineers and other data roles in the Blip ecosystem that eventually need to treat or cross-reference data in some way to answer business questions.

Some of your duties will be:

Design, code and run automated tests with some manual tests if automation is not possible.
Build and manage the Big Data environment through the data platform, enabling other data roles to operate it more easily and with less complexity;
Value the quality and compliance of the data contained in the platform;
Contribute to a culture of technical collaboration and scalable and resilient systems;
Integrate new data pipelines into the data platform, ensuring consistency in platform design patterns.
Follow the standards and processes agreed upon in existing company policies and regulations;
Work towards tight integration between systems and data models

Requirements And Qualifications

What we expect from you:

Experience with databases such as SQL, Snowflake, Postgre, for example;
Experience with Python and Spark and extensive knowledge in object-oriented and functional methodologies;
Experience building REST services;
Hands-on experience with data pipeline tools in cloud-based environments like Airflow
Strong understanding of various data formats such as CSV, XML, JSON, etc;
Have experience with the Git source control system and the ability to help others with troubleshooting;
Have experience working with CI/CD;
Experience with open source data warehouse tools;
Experience in developing some Azure cloud data platform;
Experience with micro services

It will be a plus if you have:

Experience with Kubernetes, Hadoop or Docker

